---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'How much does a website cost in 2026?';
const description = 'An honest comparison: DIY vs template vs freelance vs agency. What really drives the price — and what is a myth.';

const publishDate = '2026-03-15';
const readTime = 9;
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  ogType="article"
  ogImage="/og-default.png"
  lang="en"
  frPath="/journal/combien-coute-un-site-web"
  enPath="/en/blog/how-much-does-a-website-cost"
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative w-full bg-[#0D0D0D] px-6 py-16 md:px-8 md:py-24 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10" style="background-image: radial-gradient(circle, white 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-3xl z-10">
      <a href="/en/blog" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-neutral-300 hover:text-white transition-colors mb-8">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 16l-4-4m0 0l4-4m-4 4h18" /></svg>
        Back to blog
      </a>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <span class="inline-block rounded-full border border-[var(--color-accent)]/30 bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[var(--color-accent)]">Business</span>
        <span class="text-sm text-neutral-400">March 15, 2026</span>
        <span class="text-sm text-neutral-400">•</span>
        <span class="text-sm text-neutral-400">{readTime} min read</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-white md:text-5xl">{title}</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-300 md:text-xl leading-relaxed">{description}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ARTICLE BODY -->
  <section class="w-full bg-[var(--color-bg)] px-6 py-16 md:px-8 md:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <article class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-[var(--color-border)] p-8 md:p-12 shadow-sm">
        <div class="prose max-w-none">

          <nav class="mb-12 rounded-xl bg-[var(--color-bg-alt)] border border-[var(--color-border)] p-6 not-prose">
            <p class="mb-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">In this article</p>
            <ol class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li><a href="#categories" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline font-medium">1. The 4 main cost categories</a></li>
              <li><a href="#comparison" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline font-medium">2. Full comparison table</a></li>
              <li><a href="#factors" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline font-medium">3. What actually drives the price</a></li>
              <li><a href="#free" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline font-medium">4. What costs nothing (contrary to popular belief)</a></li>
              <li><a href="#hidden" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline font-medium">5. Hidden costs to watch out for</a></li>
              <li><a href="#conclusion" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline font-medium">6. So, what should you budget?</a></li>
            </ol>
          </nav>

          <p class="lead text-lg text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-8">
            "How much does a website cost?" That's almost certainly one of the first questions you've typed into Google. The answer you'll get depends entirely on who's answering. An agency will say €5,000. A Wix ad will say €0. The truth sits somewhere in between — and it's worth understanding why.
          </p>

          <h2 id="categories" class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mt-12 mb-6">1. The 4 main cost categories</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-6">A website budget breaks down into four distinct categories — and you won't always need all four.</p>

          <div class="not-prose grid gap-4 mb-8">
            {[
              { label: "Design & build", desc: "Someone has to create the pages, structure, and visual identity. This is where most of the cost lives." },
              { label: "Hosting", desc: "The server where your site lives. Between €5/month (shared) and €50+/month (dedicated)." },
              { label: "Domain name", desc: "Your .com or .fr address. Roughly €10–15/year." },
              { label: "Maintenance", desc: "Updates, security, backups. Often forgotten but crucial — especially with WordPress." },
            ].map(({ label, desc }) => (
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg-alt)] p-4">
                <div class="font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-1">{label}</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{desc}</div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>

          <h2 id="comparison" class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mt-12 mb-6">2. Full comparison: DIY vs template vs freelance vs agency</h2>

          <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto mb-8">
            <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-[var(--color-bg-alt)]">
                  <th class="text-left p-3 border border-[var(--color-border)] font-bold text-[var(--color-text)]">Option</th>
                  <th class="text-left p-3 border border-[var(--color-border)] font-bold text-[var(--color-text)]">Cost</th>
                  <th class="text-left p-3 border border-[var(--color-border)] font-bold text-[var(--color-text)]">Quality</th>
                  <th class="text-left p-3 border border-[var(--color-border)] font-bold text-[var(--color-text)]">SEO</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                {[
                  ["Wix / Squarespace (DIY)", "€0–30/month", "⭐⭐", "⭐⭐"],
                  ["WordPress + template", "€200–800", "⭐⭐⭐", "⭐⭐⭐"],
                  ["Freelance (custom)", "€490–2,000", "⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐", "⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐"],
                  ["Web agency", "€3,000–15,000", "⭐⭐⭐⭐", "⭐⭐⭐⭐"],
                ].map(([opt, cost, quality, seo], i) => (
                  <tr class={i % 2 === 0 ? 'bg-white' : 'bg-[var(--color-bg-alt)]'}>
                    <td class="p-3 border border-[var(--color-border)] font-medium text-[var(--color-text)]">{opt}</td>
                    <td class="p-3 border border-[var(--color-border)] text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{cost}</td>
                    <td class="p-3 border border-[var(--color-border)] text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{quality}</td>
                    <td class="p-3 border border-[var(--color-border)] text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{seo}</td>
                  </tr>
                ))}
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <h2 id="factors" class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mt-12 mb-6">3. What actually drives the price</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-4">Three main factors inflate a website price:</p>
          <ul class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-2 mb-8 list-disc list-inside">
            <li><strong>Number of pages.</strong> A 1-page showcase costs much less than a 10-page site with a blog.</li>
            <li><strong>Custom functionality.</strong> Booking system, e-commerce, customer area — each adds complexity.</li>
            <li><strong>Brand identity.</strong> Starting from scratch with no logo, no colours, no defined tone takes more time than working from an existing brief.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="free" class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mt-12 mb-6">4. What costs nothing (contrary to popular belief)</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-4">SEO. Not the expensive "SEO agency" kind — but technical SEO. A well-built site (clean structure, fast loading, Schema.org markup, sitemap) ranks better than a badly-built site regardless of how much was spent on "SEO work."</p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-8">A €490 site from me comes with better technical SEO than most €3,000 WordPress sites built with Elementor. Performance matters more than budget.</p>

          <h2 id="hidden" class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mt-12 mb-6">5. Hidden costs to watch out for</h2>
          <div class="not-prose rounded-xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-6 mb-8">
            <p class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-3">⚠️ The true cost of "cheap" options</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-amber-700">
              <li>• WordPress hosting: €5–20/month × 12 = €60–240/year, forever</li>
              <li>• Premium plugins: often €50–200/year each</li>
              <li>• Developer to fix updates that break the site: €100–300 per incident</li>
              <li>• Lost clients from a slow, outdated site: immeasurable</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h2 id="conclusion" class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mt-12 mb-6">6. So, what should you budget?</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-4">For a small business, craftsperson, or freelancer, here's the honest breakdown:</p>
          <ul class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] space-y-2 mb-8 list-disc list-inside">
            <li><strong>€490</strong> — 1–3 page custom site, contact form, basic SEO. Enough to get started and look professional.</li>
            <li><strong>€1,290</strong> — 4–8 pages, blog, advanced SEO, everything a growing business needs.</li>
            <li><strong>€1,990+</strong> — booking, e-commerce, or any complex custom requirement.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">All of these include 1 year of hosting, domain, SSL, and maintenance. No hidden recurring fees.</p>

          <div class="not-prose mt-12 rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-accent)]/20 bg-[var(--color-accent-light)] p-6 text-center">
            <p class="font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-4">Want a quote for your project?</p>
            <a href="/en/contact" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-xl bg-[var(--color-accent)] px-6 py-3 font-semibold text-white transition-all hover:bg-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">
              Get a free quote →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
